name: Amie Joy
text: Nice employees wonderful management. Pizza was amazing

name: Jared Dowland
text: Convenient location...not the most pretty though.  Very friendly, professional service.  Pizza was great, and ZERO wait for my pickup order. I would order from them again!

name: lil lady
text: Best pizza in Tillicum!! And they allow I to use the deasl on their app in this store,  coupons and discounts are honored no problem they also have a great deal on a carry out large pizza with 2 toppings for about 8 something it rounds out …More

name: Jeff Waldrop
text: Staff.... super friendly.  Pizza....excellent.  I'd give 5 stars but theres misques from time to time with how many extras, like sauces, thy hat are ordered vs how many actually make it in the box.  Still not gonna keep me from enjoying this awesome pizza.

name: Taina Gata
text: Favorite fast pizza. Amazing and tasteful pizza . Very friendly customer service.

name: Yoosteen
text: Nice little pizza shop. Everything was made where you can visually see and they bake the pizza while you wait. Sure everyone would want their order as soon as they placed it, but just knowing it was made fresh, is good. It wasn't the …More

name: Jeff M
text: Very poor service, Sounds like the employees are running around playing games in the background. More interesting in playing then taking customers orders. Sounds like they need to hire a new manager. …More

name: stephanie schafer
text: I live not even a minute away and when I get a notification that my pizza is on its way it still takes a half hour to get there and shows up cold.  It's really to bad you're the only pizza place that delivers. Guess I should start using uber eats. At least their food shows up hot.

name: Annie Smith
text: I just placed an order for delivery with a Papa John's employee named Ariel. Probably the best interaction with a person at a food joint since moving to Washington 7 months ago. Extremely kind and helpful. Very, very appreciated.

name: Bartimaeus
text: Number of toppings was excellent, however, they can sometimes be slow.

name: V Lopez
text: Pretty much every Friday or Saturday I order pizza. I live very close to this place so I check their deals on the phone   make the order online and pick up. Usually take 15 to 20min and is always muy bueno. Also when I have points  the brownie is the best choice for only 10 points.

name: Guy Johnson
text: I ordered one large pizza and an order of bread sticks. Long story short my wife and I waited an hour while checking the tracker repeatedly, only for my order to not arrive. I made a phone call to the store and the employee to tell me …More

name: Terri Scott
text: I like their pizza, but can't order one when they don't answer the phone. Been calling for an hour. Are they closed???

name: Tina WestMontalbano
text: Just say no.  Do not order pizza here. You will be waiting forever and a year for a pizza. The service is horrible and slow. I have given this restaurant over 5 tries to get it right. They can't! They leave you on hold and forget you are on hold. I rather eat a PB &J and call it a night. I am so over pizza in this state.

name: Reflective Auto Detailing
text: Horrible pizza, very rude employee and manager after they messed up the pizza order for me and my hungry 9 yr old son. The pizza took a 70 min when it was supposed to be 35 min. I was also told by the driver that the manager banned me from ordering pizza from them again...lol...read my review again and see if im really worried at all.

name: Jonathan Silberstein
text: This place sucks i waited 2 hours for a pizza then told we need to make it again. Dont waste your time or mobey here

name: Josh
text: Never gonna order from here again! They would not honor their coupons and I get attitude from the papa johns employees.... Smh that's ok with me, looks like my business will be better accepted elsewhere. I added a photo of the papa's trio coupon that this store didn't believe existed.

name: Jake McKeen
text: Order delivery a lot, and never have any issues. Always great pizza

name: Leah Scibelli-Dubois
text: Pizza was good, very slow customer service.

name: Alberto Suarez
text: Great service pretty friendly pizza was hot and well cooked

name: Swift Clearly
text: In most cases I don't do bad review but if you don't like your job don't take it out on the customer furthermore why allow you workers to be so rude? God bless

name: reese lawson
text: Little bit ridiculous a medium pizza is $13 and a delivery fee of $3 on line but the exact same pizza when you call them is $22 and a $5 delivery fee

name: x Angel
text: The pizza is the absolute best, they are VERY generous with the bacon.

name: Alexys
text: This Papa John's is not very well taken care of. I've only order pizza from this location once and it was alright. Nothing really special about this place.

name: Cipriano Armijo
text: Excellent customer service

name: Veronica E
text: Love the pizza hate the price but love seeing deals pop up in my text messages and emails

name: Joel W
text: I've been waiting for 2 hours for my food I still haven't received it, the staff was rude on the phone they instantly put me on hold as soon as they picked up.

name: Kathia Holly
text: They need new manager team, the manager there sarah is very rude and unprofessional.

name: Johannah Little
text: Ordered from this location online, they deducted the money from my bank account and then when I went to pick up my order they said they never received an order because they're closed. How can they take money from your account online if they're closed?

name: Fher Evia
text:

Buenazas las pizzas
